00:11:53.060 --> 00:11:56.560
So as a sidebar,
provisioning profiles are the

00:11:56.600 --> 00:12:00.760
key to allowing an application
to run on the iPhone.

00:12:00.830 --> 00:12:03.860
So this is why it's important that
iPhone Configuration Utility allows

00:12:03.970 --> 00:12:09.850
you to install both applications and
their associated provisioning profiles.

00:12:10.060 --> 00:12:13.640
Provisioning profiles have two
important pieces of information.

00:12:13.730 --> 00:12:17.200
The first being the
application creator's identity.

00:12:17.240 --> 00:12:21.450
This is a signing certificate,
which you use when you're signing the

00:12:21.450 --> 00:12:25.800
application that you're installing,
that you intend to give out.

00:12:26.250 --> 00:12:30.380
and this gives your users authentication
so that they can know that this

00:12:30.380 --> 00:12:33.680
application actually came from you.

00:12:34.980 --> 00:12:37.780
The second important piece
of information is a list of

00:12:37.780 --> 00:12:41.660
Universal Device Identifiers,
or UDIDs.

00:12:41.710 --> 00:12:45.680
These are the ones that I mentioned
earlier that we saw in our Summary tab.

00:12:45.790 --> 00:12:50.680
And what this gives the iPhone,
as well as you as IT individuals,

00:12:50.780 --> 00:12:55.200
is authorization so that the application
that you've signed with this provisioning

00:12:55.200 --> 00:13:01.730
profile will only run on the iPhones
that are in this list of UDIDs.

00:13:01.860 --> 00:13:06.240
So this is a very important
thing for IT management.

00:13:06.660 --> 00:13:08.560
And of course,
this wouldn't make much difference

00:13:08.560 --> 00:13:11.090
if somebody could go in and fool
with the contents of the file.

00:13:11.200 --> 00:13:15.660
So provisioning profiles are
also signed to prevent tampering.

